   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1872_10_02_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_H_C_Bock_Hamburg_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>via Brindisi. Hamburg, 2nd Oct. 1872.<lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler &amp;
                Co.<lb/>Yokohama,<lb/>Japan.<lb/>I last wrote to you on 1st August of this month, a
                letter that <lb/>I hope you have in your hands and I am hereby <lb/>confirming its
                contents. Since sending that letter<lb/>I have had the pleasure of receiving your
                esteemed<lb/>letters from 11th June, 6th July and two from 6th August of this year.
                <lb/>From the last-mentioned missive I gathered your remittance of <lb/>
            <table>
               <row>
                  <cell>Rrth 45,000＂-</cell>
                  <cell>à vista - on Deutsche Bank, Aktien Ges.
                            Berlin,<lb/>for which I gratefully credited you after deducting
                            <lb/>Rthl. 22„ 15 Sgr- for stamps and</cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell>67.15</cell>
                  <cell>＂ 45„ _„ for broker’s fees</cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell>with Rrth 44,932„ 15 Sgr </cell>
               </row>
            </table> ⟨M116⟩<lb/>
            <table>
               <row>
                  <cell>on Thaler-Account. . . . . . . </cell>
                  <cell>Rrth 32,932.15.-</cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell>＂ Banco-Account: Bo₻ 21,110„8 à 149 5/16 % </cell>
                  <cell>＂ 12,000„-</cell>
               </row>
            </table> ⟨shall be Bo₻ 24,110.8⟩<lb/>
            <lb/>and ask you to book this conformly. <lb/>The contents of the remainder of your
                esteemed letters <lb/>do not need any further reply as they have been dealt with.
                <lb/>Expressing my hope that by the time you receive these <lb/>lines you will have
                succeeded in selling from my <lb/>warehouse, I am taking my leave as there is no
                need<lb/>for further notices, Yours sincerely<lb/>H. C. Bock<lb/>P.
                S.<lb/>Definitely liquidate my warehouses, with Hiogo<lb/>+ Nagasaki, before the end
                of the year. <lb/>HB[?]</p>
         <pb facs="1872_10_02_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_H_C_Bock_Hamburg_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <pb facs="1872_10_02_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_H_C_Bock_Hamburg_3.tif" n="3"/>
